definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  2-hydroxyisobutyrate + H+ -eq- CO2 + 2-propanol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-hydroxy-2-methyl-1,3-dicarbonate + H+ -eq- CO2 + L-lactate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4,5-dihydroxyphthalate -eq- 3,4-dihydroxybenzoate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  gallate + H(+) -eq- CO(2) + pyrogallol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-hydroxybenzoate + H(+) -eq- CO(2) + phenol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-oxopent-3-ene-1,2,5-tricarboxylate -eq- 2-oxohept-3-enedioate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trans-glutaconyl-CoA + H(+) -eq- but-2-enoyl-CoA + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,4-dihydroxy-hept-trans-2-ene-1,7-dioate -eq- pyruvate + succinic semialdehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (3E)-4-(2-carboxyphenyl)-2-oxobut-3-enoate -eq- 2-carboxybenzaldehyde + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  fumarate + toluene -eq- 2-benzylsuccinate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-hydroxycyclohex-1-ene-1-carboxyl-CoA + H2O -eq- 2,6-dihydroxycyclohexane-1-carboxyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trans-4-(1'-hydroxynaphth-2'-yl)-2-oxobut-3-enoate + H2O -eq- pyruvate + 1-hydroxy-2-naphthaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  E-phenylitaconyl-CoA + H2O -eq- (hydroxymethylphenyl)succinyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trans-4-(2-(3-hydroxy)-thionaphthenyl)-2-oxo-3-butenoate + H2O -eq- pyruvate + 3-hydroxy-2-formylbenzothiophene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cyclohex-1-ene-1-carboxyl-CoA + H2O -eq- 2-hydroxycyclohexane-1-carboxyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alkene-CoA + H2O -eq- alcohol-CoA. Substrates are crotonoyl-CoA (producing 3-hydroxyacyl-CoA) and 2,3-didehydro-pimeloyl-CoA (producing 3-hydroxypimeloyl-CoA).

Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxo-3-enoate-4-benzenoid + H2O -eq- pyruvate + benzaldehyde derivative. Substrates are (3E)-4-(5-amino-2-hydroxy-phenyl)-2-oxo-but-3-ene-1-oic-acid (forms 5-aminosalicylaldehyde) and trans-o-hydroxybenzylidenepyruvate (forms salicylaldehyde).
Catalysis of the reaction -  (trans)-phenylacetaldoxime -eq- H(2)O + phenylacetonitrile.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-methyl-5-hydroxy-6-(3-carboxy-3-oxopropenyl)-1H-2-pyridon + H2O -eq- 2-oxobut-3-enanoate + 2,5,6-trihydroxy-3-methylpyridine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-hydroxyisobutyrate -eq- H2O + methacrylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-2-oxohept-3-ene-1,7-dioate + H2O -eq- 2,4-dihydroxy-hept-trans-2-ene-1,7-dioate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetaldehyde -eq- acetylene + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  lactoyl-CoA -eq- acryloyl-CoA + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  urea -eq- cyanamide + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an aliphatic amide -eq- a nitrile + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cyclohexa-1,5-diene-1-carbonyl-CoA + H(2)O -eq- 6-hydroxycyclohex-1-enecarbonyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (hydroxyamino)benzene -eq- 2-aminophenol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  triethanolamine -eq- diethanolamine + acetaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-methionine -eq- methanethiol + NH3 + 2-oxobutanoate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane -eq- HCl + unsym-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene. 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane is also known as DDMS -  unsym-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene is also known as DDNU.
Catalysis of the elimination of HCl from a chloro- or bromopropanol, yielding an epoxypropane.

Catalysis of the reaction -  1,1-dichloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane -eq- HCl + 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene. 1,1-dichloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane is also known as DDD -  1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene is also known as DDMU.
Catalysis of the reaction -  gamma-hexachlorocyclohexane + HCl -eq- 1,3(R),4(S),5(S),6(R)-pentachlorocyclohexene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-chloro-1,2,4-trihydroxybenzene -eq- Cl- + H+ + 2-hydroxy-1,4-benzoquinone.
Catalysis of the elimination of HCl from a chloropropanol, yielding an epoxypropane.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,1,1-trichloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane -eq- 1,1-dichloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethylene + chloride + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  dichloromethane + H(2)O -eq- 2 chloride + formaldehyde + 2 H(+).

Catalysis of the reaction -  alkylphosphonic acid -eq- R-CH3 + phosphate. Substrates include aminomethylphosphonic acid (AMPA) (forms methylamine), dimethylphosphinic acid (forms methylphosphonic acid), glyphosate (forms sarcosine) and methylphosphonic acid (forms phosphate).
Catalysis of the reaction -  R-Hg+ + H+ -eq- R-H + Hg2+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-hydroxy-2 H-benzo[h]chromene-2-carboxylate -eq- cis -4-(1'-hydroxynaphth-2'-yl)-2-oxobut-3-enoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-mandelate -eq- (R)-mandelate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-4-(2-(3-hydroxy)-thionaphthenyl)-2-oxo-3-butenoate -eq- trans-4-(2-(3-hydroxy)-thionaphthenyl)-2-oxo-3-butenoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-sulfomuconate -eq- 4-sulfolactone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-hydroxytetrahydrofuran -eq- 4-hydroxybutyraldehyde.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2-hydroxychromene-2-carboxylate -eq- (3E)-4-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-2-oxobut-3-enoate. (3E)-4-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-2-oxobut-3-enoate is also known as trans-o-hydroxybenzylidenepyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  styrene oxide -eq- phenylacetaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-pinene -eq- limonene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  pinocarveol -eq- carveol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,5-dihydro-5-oxofuran-2-acetate -eq- cis,cis-hexadienedioate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-chloro-2,5-dihydro-5-oxofuran-2-acetate -eq- 3-chloro-cis,cis-muconate.
